The paper deals with a combinatorial problem and presents an algorithmic solution for a deductive game, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of strategies and approximation algorithms also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also deals with game theory and combinatorics, which could place it in the sub-categories of game theory (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
